---
import '../styles/global.css';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Material+Symbols+Outlined:opsz,wght,FILL,GRAD@20..48,100..700,0..1,-50..200" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Geist:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>

  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - Sky States</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Read the Sky States privacy policy. Learn how we secure your data, protect student privacy, and enforce strict zero-SSN collection policies." />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://skystates.us/privacy-policy" />
  
  
</head>
<body class="bg-surface text-on-surface font-body-md overflow-x-hidden">
  <Header />
  <main class="mt-20">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-surface-bright text-center px-6 border-b border-outline-variant/10">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">
        <span class="bg-primary/10 text-primary px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full font-label-md text-label-md tracking-wide uppercase font-bold">Data Trust</span>
        <h1 class="font-headline-xl text-5xl font-bold text-on-background leading-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-secondary font-body-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">At Sky States, we hold student data security and privacy to institutional standards. Read our comprehensive policies below.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Policy Content -->
    <section class="py-section-gap max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-12">
      
      <!-- Section 1: Security Commitment -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary">lock</span>
          1. Security Commitment & Non-Collection of SSNs
        </h2>
        <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Sky States is committed to protecting your personal information. We enforce a strict policy regarding sensitive personal identifiers: <strong>Sky States does NOT collect, store, or process Social Security Numbers (SSN)</strong> or equivalent national identification numbers from our students or applicants.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: Data We Collect -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary">database</span>
          2. Information We Collect
        </h2>
        <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We collect minimal personal details necessary to facilitate your training, career services, and billing:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Name, professional email address, phone number, and physical address.</li>
          <li><strong>Academic & Professional History:</strong> Resume, LinkedIn URL, and academic/STEM background to tailor career placement.</li>
          <li><strong>Billing Information:</strong> Payments are securely processed via certified, PCI-compliant third-party gateways (e.g., Stripe). Sky States does not store your credit card credentials on our servers.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: Screen Share and Live Labs -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary">screen_share</span>
          3. Screen Share & Live Class Interaction
        </h2>
        <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          During our live weekend instruction, interactive labs, and capstone project evaluations, students may be requested to share their screens. This is conducted solely for real-time pedagogical support, code debugging, and skills assessment. Screen sharing sessions are never recorded without explicit, prior student consent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: Data Retention & Protection -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary">shield</span>
          4. Data Protection Standards
        </h2>
        <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          All data transmitted to or from the Sky States platform is encrypted in transit using industry-standard SSL/TLS technology. Access to student records is strictly restricted to authorized educational mentors and career services coordinators.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5: Contact Our Privacy Team -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary">contact_support</span>
          5. Privacy Inquiries
        </h2>
        <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          For any questions, modifications, or deletion requests regarding your personal data records, please reach out directly to our privacy officer at <a href="mailto:info@skystates.us" class="text-primary font-semibold hover:underline">info@skystates.us</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
